<span class="date"><a href="mailto:kwill@rpgplanet.com">Kwill</a> | 1/23/2001 - 8:56<br></span><br>
<span class="news"><font color="9999cc"></span></font>
<span class="news">Absor reports on the official Sony boards that they will not be making any changes to the game for some time: <blockquote><i>For at least a few weeks we will be doing some internal work that will prevent us from making any updates to the
                          game unless they are critical (and there are no such things that we know of at this time).<br><br>

                          We will still be taking in reports about bugs and other suggestions for change (such as the Class Talk stuff), but
                          we won’t be making any changes to the game. And the two-week timeframe is only a guess at the moment, it
                          could go longer.<br><br>

                          While this means there will be no changes to the game during this time, we will still be maintaining the servers, the
                          physical hardware, and all other aspects of the game. We are just not changing any aspects of the game software
                          itself.</i></blockquote>
Brad (Aradune) added this clarification:<blockquote><i>

                          I just wanted to add a bit more detail to what Absor's posted.<br><br>

                          Basically, we're going through and spending a focussed 2 weeks to evaluate, document, and plan, getting us ready
                          for the remainder of this year. I can't be too specific yet, because it's too early to make major announcements, but
                          this would include finishing up design for future free zones, planning out engine mods to keep EQ current, as well as
                          anything major EQ related to be released in the next year or so.<br><br>

                          So, bottom line, we're planning and documenting as opposed to implementing during this period.<br><br>

                          What that really means for you guys, essentially, is you won't see a patch for 2-3 weeks unless an emergency
                          arises. That's all.</i></blockquote>
</span></p>
